abstract_summ: The modelled impact without a travel ban results in more than 2000 cases and about 400 deaths, if the epidemic remained localised to China and no importations from other countries occurred.METHODS: We used disease incidence data from China and air travel passenger movements between China and Australia during and after the epidemic peak in China, derived from incoming passenger arrival cards.We used disease incidence data from China and air travel passenger movements between China and Australia, derived from incoming passenger arrival cards.This research demonstrates the effectiveness of travel bans applied to countries with high disease incidence.RESULTS: The modelled epidemic with the full ban fitted the observed incidence of cases well, predicting 57 cases on March 6(th) in Australia, compared to 66 observed on this date, however we did not account for imported cases from other countries.
